 {"id":"bd-uy5a","title":"sysv: execute sysv_ipc_ops.json fixture family through harness matrix","description":"Concrete gap: crates/frankenlibc-harness/tests/sysv_ipc_ops_conformance_test.rs currently exercises SysV IPC fixtures only through frankenlibc_fixture_exec. Add isolated harness subprocess coverage for tests/conformance/fixtures/sysv_ipc_ops.json, assert expected_output and host parity in strict/hardened modes, and fix any subprocess-path regressions the matrix run exposes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"AmberSignal","created_at":"2026-04-21T04:38:39.690413835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T14:14:57.898785473Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T14:14:57.896624321Z","close_reason":"Switched sysv_ipc_ops fixture coverage to the isolated harness conformance matrix subprocess path and verified locally plus via rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-v01ak","title":"PORT: crypt_r/rn/ra + crypt_gensalt/_r/_rn/_ra + xcrypt_r/_gensalt/_gensalt_r","description":"Add the remaining libcrypt re-entrant + gensalt API to close the libcrypt parity gap. Our existing crypt() supports MD5/SHA-256/SHA-512 already; build on it. (1) crypt_r(key, salt, *data) -> *mut c_char: call crypt(), copy the result string into data->output (which sits at offset 0 of struct crypt_data per glibc and libxcrypt), return data as *mut c_char. (2) crypt_rn(key, salt, *data, size) -> *mut c_char: like crypt_r with explicit size; refuse if size < result length. (3) crypt_ra(key, salt, **data, *size) -> *mut c_char: auto-allocating version; if *data NULL or *size too small, malloc 384 bytes (CRYPT_OUTPUT_SIZE). (4) crypt_gensalt(prefix, count, *rbytes, nrbytes) -> *mut c_char: generate a salt string for the requested algorithm (default $6$ when prefix is NULL/empty) using rbytes as a random source; return pointer to a static thread-local buffer. (5) crypt_gensalt_r(prefix, count, *rbytes, nrbytes, *output, output_size) -> *mut c_char: same into caller buffer. (6) crypt_gensalt_rn(...) -> alias of _r. (7) crypt_gensalt_ra(prefix, count, *rbytes, nrbytes) -> *mut c_char: malloc + format. (8)/(9)/(10) xcrypt_r / xcrypt_gensalt / xcrypt_gensalt_r — aliases.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T18:01:27.904145785Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T18:01:27.904145785Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
